  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "While opinions on the most inspirational movies can vary, here\u2019s a list of ten films from the 21st century that are often cited for their inspirational themes, storytelling, and impact. These movies span different genres and styles but all offer compelling narratives of perseverance, courage, and hope:\n\n1. **The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)** - Starring Will Smith, this biographical drama follows the true story of Chris Gardner's journey from homelessness to becoming a successful stockbroker.\n\n2. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)** - This film tells the story of an Indian teenager from the slums who competes on a game show, showcasing themes of destiny and perseverance.\n\n3. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)** - A biographical drama about John Nash, a Nobel Laureate in Economics, dealing with schizophrenia and showcasing resilience in the face of adversity.\n\n4. **Life of Pi (2012)** - Based on the novel, this film combines stunning visuals with a survival story that explores faith and friendship in the face of overwhelming odds.\n\n5. **Million Dollar Baby (2004)** - Directed by Clint Eastwood, it\u2019s an emotional story about a determined female boxer and her quest for respect and success.\n\n6. **The Intouchables (2011)** - A heartwarming French film based on a true story about the friendship between a disabled man and his caregiver from a completely different background.\n\n7. **Freedom Writers (2007)** - Inspired by real events, this film follows a teacher who transforms her at-risk students' lives through writing and understanding.\n\n8. **The King\u2019s Speech (2010)** - This historical drama tells the story of King George VI and his struggle with a speech impediment, highlighting his efforts to overcome it during a critical period.\n\n9. **The Blind Side (2009)** - Based on the true story of Michael Oher, this film shows the impact of kindness and opportunity on a young man's life through the support of a caring family.\n\n10. **Hidden Figures (2016)** - A biographical drama that celebrates the contributions of three African-American women mathematicians who played crucial roles at NASA during the Space Race.\n\nThese films are celebrated for their uplifting narratives and the way they inspire audiences to reflect on human potential and resilience.",
